    <profile name="Rage Driven" typeId="fab4-73e7-0aea-16c7" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="bd1a-c1b9-f52d-dae5">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="3fef-df7c-7ca9-43cf">[Passive]: Every time this model loses a hit point, gain 1 energy.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="ZAPP!" typeId="fab4-73e7-0aea-16c7" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="30bd-40ce-0b21-092c">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="3fef-df7c-7ca9-43cf">[Fast, Cost 0]: After this Fighter takes a combat action, as a fast ability, you may deal 1 damage with Pierce 2 to an enemy Fighter that it is in contact with.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Curse" typeId="fab4-73e7-0aea-16c7" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="2bb1-06f3-2bf7-ce57">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="3fef-df7c-7ca9-43cf">[Combat Action: Cost 1-5]: Spend up to 5 energy and deal that much deadly damage to this Fighter. Then select an enemy Fighter within 8”. Deal damage to that Fighter equal to the amount of energy spent (they may save at Pierce 0). For each Cultist model that was destroyed this way, deal 1 additional deadly damage to the target. This ability may only be used once per turn.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Spite Capacitors" typeId="fab4-73e7-0aea-16c7" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="94fc-44db-7a2f-8b87">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="3fef-df7c-7ca9-43cf">When this Fighter takes damage from a ranged attack, before rolling saves, you may choose to convert up to 4 of that damage to deadly damage (roll this many fewer saves). The attacking Fighter takes an amount of damage equal to the deadly damage taken this way. (They may save against this at Pierce 0). If this Fighter is destroyed by deadly damage taken this way, also deal 1 Deadly Damage to the attacking Fighter. You may not use both this ability and “Power to Shields!” for the same attack.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
  </sharedProfiles>
